{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dbd959cd-9f6f-4951-b109-9d3efa3ecbec","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n**In .NET 10, `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed.** The SDK runs `dotnet test` through Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. Your project just needs:\n\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — tells MSTest to build as an MTP executable (you already have this)\n- **`OutputType Exe`** — required for the MTP runner entry point (you already have this)\n\nThat's it. Run `dotnet test` and it will use MTP automatically. If you ever need to fall back to the legacy VSTest pipeline, you can set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>false</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`, but the default in .NET 10 is MTP.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27b31865-291c-42f1-8081-72f80d0f1a86","outputTokens":188,"requestId":"BD1A:1BD126:1C61BF7:201D360:6A07C5C0"},"id":"84ce80d8-a87a-43b7-a54b-fbab1fcbcff5","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:17:57.724Z","parentId":"7a956b1c-65f7-4936-8d71-ae2afd84ee6c"}
